{{Infobox software | title = InfraKit | name = InfraKit | developer = [[Docker, Inc.]] | released = {{Start date and age|2016|10|04|df=yes/no}} | discontinued = | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2016|07|14|df=yes/no}} | latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | status = | programming language = [[Go (programming language)|Go]] | operating system = [[Linux]] | platform = [[x86-64]] | genre = [[Operating-system-level virtualization]] | license = [[Apache License]] 2.0 | website = {{URL|https://github.com/docker/infrakit/}} }}
'''InfraKit''' is an [[Open-source software|open-source]] project that is part of the larger [[Docker (software)|Docker]] application container software project. The project was formally announced for Docker by its creator [[Solomon Hykes]] at the [[LinuxCon|Linuxcon]] [[European Union|EU]] 2016 event. InfraKit was originally called 'libmachete' and was renamed by Docker developers in October 2016.
According to the project's [[GitHub]] description, InfraKit is a toolkit for creating and managing declarative, self-healing infrastructure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://github.com/docker/infrakit|title=docker/infrakit|website=GitHub|access-date=2016-10-07}}</ref> InfraKit consists of several core elements which include, instances, groups and flavors. Groups are collections of instances while flavors are specific groups built for a certain purpose. The InfraKit model works as a set of plugins that can be used to monitor Docker infrastructure. In the event of a failure or a node falling out of a set policy, the self-healing element of InfraKit enables remediation.
